What Guests Said About Bukovel:

  • 10

    I was very impressed by the quality and number of ski-lifts...

    I was very impressed by the quality and number of ski-lifts (Austrian make) and the very modern ski-pass scanners that would scan your ticket through your jacket or glove. The ski area is very large with many different ski runs available. Many places to rent skis at, again very well set up. Many restaurants to choose from, also on the slopes, including high end restaurants. Prices are generally more expensive, as to be expected from such a place, but still very reasonable and affordable by European standards.
    Jorrit
    Ukraine
  • 8.0

    The infrastructure could use a little updating, especially...

    The infrastructure could use a little updating, especially ski lifts. The prices are ridiculous, taxi ride can take two minutes, but you will pay for it 250 UAH regardless, same goes for food and accommodations. This is surely the most expensive place in Ukraine.
    Tetiana
    Ukraine
  • 6.0

    Bukovel is Ukraine's premier ski resort, which if you...

    Bukovel is Ukraine's premier ski resort, which if you compare to European or North American resorts you will be sorely disappointed. It is poorly laid out, and getting very jumbled now. In Ukraine however, there is little choice, so it is full year round, especially now with the war, there are whole armies of young men hiding away from conscription, and who could blame them. Some lifts offer in summer, and you can go up the mountains fir hiking, hiking, or just relaxing. Winter snow is mostly man made, augmented by some snow fall, but the elevation is not high. There are many restaurants, but not enough, plenty of hotels, not a lot of really good ones, but certainly adequate. By Western standards they are inexpensive, but by local standards they are severely overpriced.
    A
    Aussie 1965
    Australia
  • 8.0

    Altogether Bukovel was good.

    Altogether Bukovel was good. The slopes were really good - I would say better that in Scandinavia (maybe Are is similar), Sakapone and Slovakia. Freeride zones were my favorite was we got lot on new snow. Other slopes were maintained well. Good places to eat or to have bear. Center ski rent was disaster - bad equipment and long queues. recommend to rent from some smaller places. Go skiing as early as possible, approx.. 11 most of people will arrive and then there are some lifts where you need to wait couple of minutes. Our hotel was 2 km from the center and taxi cost 5-6 € one way. In the center we did not find any restaurants except Caiser witch was with good food but pit price. Also local liquor that they recommended was really bad even for us. Later we found local restaurants more fare from the center and they were 2 x cheaper with the same or even better quality. Walking around Bukovel was almost impossible as there was no sidewalks. We needed to walk on roads and it was quite dangerous. For nightlife the best palace was BUKA - nightclub and in other room there was cabree :) So yes I would go back there. Little Soviet time romantic mixed with modern European things.
    Marek
    Estonia
  • 6.0

    Its good city for winter entertainments however people has...

    Its good city for winter entertainments however people has made this experience not good enough as they don't speak English they are not very helpful and i hardly find my hotel and i couldn't get my ticket to play any thing easily ,, you need to know someone there or to go with group.
    Hassan

  • 10

    We visited at end of summer season, with autumn just...

How does it work?

  • 1

    It starts with a booking

    It starts with a booking

    The only way to leave a review is to first make a booking. That's how we know our reviews come from real guests who have stayed at the property.

  • 2

    Followed by a trip

    Followed by a trip

    When guests stay at the property, they check out how quiet the room is, how friendly the staff is, and more.

  • 3

    And finally, a review

    And finally, a review

    After their trip, guests tell us about their stay. We check for naughty words and verify the authenticity of all guest reviews before adding them to our site.
